name: Consumed
description: If anxiety had a face, this is how it would look like. Menacing, proud, overpowering, and invincible. I’ve been self-consumed by anxiety that it effected my relationship with my wife. I was physically there, but my mind wasn’t. I didn’t realize it at first. I thought I was attentive. I felt I was present, but in truth, my mind was wandering for answers. Answers to how the hell do I overcome this anxiety? What’s the trigger for this anxiety? Is it from my past? Do I have unresolved issues? What the hell is it?
